        {
          "type": "markdown",
          "title": "Technical Notes",
          "content": "### Route-based Code Splitting\n\nWe migrated from a monolithic bundle to route-based code splitting using `React.lazy` and `Suspense`. Each of the 12 major routes now loads independently.\n\n**Key changes:**\n- Dashboard, Settings, Analytics, and Reports are all lazy-loaded\n- Shared component library is extracted to a common chunk\n- Vendor dependencies split by usage frequency\n\n### Virtual Scrolling\n\nThe dashboard table now uses `react-window` for virtualized rendering. This handles 10,000+ rows without DOM bloat.\n\n| Metric | Before | After |\n|--------|--------|-------|\n| Render time (10k rows) | 2.4s | 45ms |\n| Memory usage | 340MB | 52MB |\n| Scroll FPS | 12 | 60 |"
        }
      ]
    },
